1
00:00:35,910 --> 00:00:38,455
It's possible that
this is the new operational site

2
00:00:38,538 --> 00:00:40,290
<i>of La Morte Bianca in the Philippines.</i>

3
00:00:48,923 --> 00:00:49,966
The Concordat.

4
00:00:50,049 --> 00:00:53,636
<i>Their goal is to establish</i>
<i>an administration here in the Philippines,</i>

5
00:00:53,720 --> 00:00:56,681
and spread their terror from here.

6
00:01:00,477 --> 00:01:02,520
<i>They immediately found the site</i>

7
00:01:02,604 --> 00:01:05,940
that Isabella
purchased as their stronghold.

8
00:01:07,108 --> 00:01:09,319
It's like… it's raining a bit.

9
00:01:09,402 --> 00:01:11,321
- Mikoy, what…
- It's drizzling?

10
00:01:11,404 --> 00:01:12,489
- So annoying.
- Is this it?

11
00:01:12,989 --> 00:01:13,948
It's raining!

12
00:01:14,032 --> 00:01:15,158
Hey, what is it?

13
00:01:16,284 --> 00:01:18,286
We already had a census last year.

14
00:01:21,873 --> 00:01:23,458
Let's go, let's go.

15
00:01:23,541 --> 00:01:24,334
You're new here.

16
00:01:26,294 --> 00:01:28,838
We need to talk to one of their people.

17
00:02:27,939 --> 00:02:29,149
You've got some nerve,

18
00:02:29,232 --> 00:02:32,360
stealing inside a mafia house.

19
00:02:32,443 --> 00:02:33,945
And you're even copying me.

20
00:02:57,051 --> 00:02:58,052
Bok.

21
00:02:59,929 --> 00:03:01,848
What's that? Do you have a problem?

22
00:03:06,978 --> 00:03:08,354
I'm just worried.

23
00:03:10,773 --> 00:03:12,275
What if,

24
00:03:12,358 --> 00:03:15,403
Chiara doesn't just want
to reconnect for information.

25
00:03:16,738 --> 00:03:20,241
And what if she gets to
talk to her father again,

26
00:03:20,325 --> 00:03:22,368
and she'll be convinced to come back.

27
00:03:29,959 --> 00:03:34,505
Bok, is what you're feeling,
a gut feeling?

28
00:03:35,423 --> 00:03:39,344
Is it coming from your heart?
Do you think she could betray us?

29
00:03:39,427 --> 00:03:40,386
Like that?

30
00:03:41,554 --> 00:03:44,349
I don't know, I'm not sure, but

31
00:03:44,432 --> 00:03:46,392
this isn't about my gut anymore.

32
00:03:47,310 --> 00:03:49,354
I'm just basing it on facts.

33
00:03:50,355 --> 00:03:53,691
She's a mob boss, and she grew up
in a crime syndicate.

34
00:03:54,234 --> 00:03:55,818
So she's used to betrayal.

35
00:03:57,153 --> 00:03:58,738
Okay, so you think

36
00:03:59,405 --> 00:04:01,741
Chiara could betray Mikoy?

37
00:04:13,795 --> 00:04:15,463
She wouldn't do that.

38
00:04:26,849 --> 00:04:28,685
I get why you're worried.

39
00:04:30,019 --> 00:04:31,896
I get why it's hard to trust.

40
00:04:33,898 --> 00:04:35,441
But she wouldn't do that.

41
00:04:35,984 --> 00:04:37,402
Chiara isn't perfect.

42
00:04:38,569 --> 00:04:40,029
And she isn't kind all the time either.

43
00:04:40,863 --> 00:04:42,824
But her heart isn't bad.

44
00:04:45,994 --> 00:04:47,453
You know, deep inside,

45
00:04:47,996 --> 00:04:51,291
all Chiara really wants
is a quiet and simple life.

46
00:04:52,583 --> 00:04:54,794
She never dreamed of becoming a criminal.

47
00:04:57,088 --> 00:05:00,216
Her dream is to be free.

48
00:05:03,344 --> 00:05:05,596
Agent Alex, you witnessed it yourself.

49
00:05:06,931 --> 00:05:09,183
You saw how she left everything behind.

50
00:05:09,767 --> 00:05:14,230
Family, name, protection,
status… what for?

51
00:05:19,485 --> 00:05:21,029
What I hold on to is,

52
00:05:22,530 --> 00:05:23,656
she loves me.

53
00:05:29,537 --> 00:05:31,039
And that's what she chose.

54
00:05:57,023 --> 00:06:00,234
You could've just said you were hungry.

55
00:06:08,618 --> 00:06:09,577
Chiara.

56
00:06:20,671 --> 00:06:22,507
By how she was raised. Does it matter?

57
00:10:23,247 --> 00:10:24,290
It's hard, isn't it?

58
00:10:28,711 --> 00:10:30,254
It's hard when,

59
00:10:30,963 --> 00:10:34,133
you love someone
who doesn't love you back.

60
00:10:42,933 --> 00:10:44,101
Because it hurts.

61
00:10:46,646 --> 00:10:48,314
You know you're drunk.

62
00:10:51,400 --> 00:10:53,319
I'm not drunk, Bok, okay?

63
00:10:53,944 --> 00:10:55,571
I still know what I'm saying.

64
00:10:58,407 --> 00:11:01,661
I'm just a little confused.

65
00:11:02,453 --> 00:11:04,372
There are so many people in the world.

66
00:11:06,415 --> 00:11:10,252
But why do you end up liking someone

67
00:11:11,128 --> 00:11:13,089
who could never like you back?

68
00:11:14,256 --> 00:11:16,384
Good thing I don't have time for that.

69
00:11:21,555 --> 00:11:24,016
Because that kind of stupidity
can make you do crazy things.

70
00:11:26,560 --> 00:11:28,312
- Agent Sianong.
- Hey!

71
00:11:30,439 --> 00:11:32,650
And your designated driver
still has work tomorrow.

72
00:11:33,192 --> 00:11:34,110
Let's go!

73
00:11:37,780 --> 00:11:38,823
Okay, fine.

74
00:11:39,448 --> 00:11:41,325
But first, I have a speech.

75
00:11:55,506 --> 00:11:56,924
- Let's go.
- Okay.

76
00:11:57,007 --> 00:11:57,842
Go.

77
00:11:57,925 --> 00:11:58,759
Hurry up.

78
00:12:23,742 --> 00:12:26,287
In a guy? What do you like?

79
00:12:26,370 --> 00:12:30,374
I like someone who's, a bit tall.

80
00:12:30,458 --> 00:12:31,709
How about personality?

81
00:12:34,295 --> 00:12:35,713
What's my favorite song?

82
00:12:35,796 --> 00:12:37,006
The one you always sing.

83
00:12:37,089 --> 00:12:37,923
What?

84
00:12:38,007 --> 00:12:41,510
"We Are in Love" by Taylor Swift.

85
00:12:44,346 --> 00:12:46,348
<i>See? Why is he invested?</i>

86
00:12:46,432 --> 00:12:47,850
<i>Why does he have so many questions?</i>

87
00:12:47,933 --> 00:12:50,269
<i>Why does he know your favorite song?</i>

88
00:12:51,228 --> 00:12:53,105
<i>Why not?</i>

89
00:13:01,947 --> 00:13:05,326
<i>As you said, he's observant.</i>
<i>Use your brain.</i>

90
00:13:05,409 --> 00:13:08,287
<i>Be a good judge of character that you are.</i>

91
00:13:12,333 --> 00:13:15,252
<i>What if it's nothing.</i>
<i>What if he's just a kind person.</i>

92
00:13:15,336 --> 00:13:18,380
<i>What if you're the only one</i>
<i>who's putting a meaning on it?</i>

93
00:13:18,464 --> 00:13:20,007
So what if I am?

94
00:13:21,675 --> 00:13:23,344
I'm in love.

95
00:13:23,427 --> 00:13:27,389
And people in love can be foolish.

96
00:13:28,265 --> 00:13:29,850
And that's okay.

97
00:13:31,143 --> 00:13:32,144
Besides,

98
00:13:32,937 --> 00:13:35,648
if he wants to get to know me better,

99
00:13:36,398 --> 00:13:37,942
why would I stop him?

100
00:14:32,913 --> 00:14:34,415
Can we talk?

101
00:14:39,753 --> 00:14:40,588
Well, that's early.

102
00:14:51,807 --> 00:14:54,894
Sorry, I know it's early, but,

103
00:14:55,686 --> 00:14:56,979
about last night.

104
00:14:57,813 --> 00:14:58,647
Mikoy.

105
00:14:58,731 --> 00:15:00,983
I'm not saying
you should trust her right away.

106
00:15:02,026 --> 00:15:05,529
I'm not saying everything
Chiara does is right either.

107
00:15:08,240 --> 00:15:09,909
Alex, I know it's hard.

108
00:15:11,702 --> 00:15:13,954
If I were in your position,
I'd probably feel the same way.

109
00:15:15,039 --> 00:15:19,543
Alex, I hope you'll also consider
the choices she's made here.

110
00:15:20,210 --> 00:15:21,921
Because she's given up so much.

111
00:15:23,422 --> 00:15:25,132
And that wasn't easy.

112
00:15:28,385 --> 00:15:31,013
Mikoy, in our line of work,
trust doesn't come easy.

113
00:15:31,764 --> 00:15:33,474
Because when we're wrong,

114
00:15:34,183 --> 00:15:36,435
people get hurt and put in danger.

115
00:15:40,189 --> 00:15:42,983
I can't promise that I'll trust her.

116
00:15:45,319 --> 00:15:46,820
But I'll try.

117
00:15:51,617 --> 00:15:52,826
Thank you.

118
00:16:08,258 --> 00:16:11,595
PINAGPALA
SPECIAL BAKESHOP

119
00:16:11,679 --> 00:16:12,846
Luisa Mae.

120
00:16:19,728 --> 00:16:21,146
Sorry about yesterday.

121
00:16:24,566 --> 00:16:26,735
I was just helping Laurence.

122
00:16:28,070 --> 00:16:29,321
Research.

123
00:16:30,322 --> 00:16:33,367
But don't think that,

124
00:16:35,995 --> 00:16:37,162
I like Sofie.

125
00:16:38,038 --> 00:16:41,250
That was just wingman duties.

126
00:16:44,044 --> 00:16:44,878
What?

127
00:16:46,380 --> 00:16:49,299
Why didn't you just say so right away?

128
00:16:50,217 --> 00:16:53,721
You know, that is so, so cute.

129
00:17:11,780 --> 00:17:13,824
Here, look at this.

130
00:17:13,907 --> 00:17:15,325
There!

131
00:17:15,409 --> 00:17:17,327
You know, I've really wanted to go there.

132
00:17:20,748 --> 00:17:22,916
I've been looking at it for days.

133
00:17:23,000 --> 00:17:24,168
And now,

134
00:17:24,251 --> 00:17:27,004
it's perfect!

135
00:17:27,588 --> 00:17:28,672
Perfect for what?

136
00:17:28,756 --> 00:17:30,883
There's a beach,

137
00:17:30,966 --> 00:17:32,301
an island,

138
00:17:32,384 --> 00:17:34,428
and camping.

139
00:17:35,012 --> 00:17:36,889
Right? And they say
the signal is weak there.

140
00:17:36,972 --> 00:17:40,017
Which means people
won't be on their phones much.

141
00:17:44,229 --> 00:17:47,733
Plus, we get the chance
to clean the shore too.

142
00:17:47,816 --> 00:17:48,734
Right?

143
00:17:49,443 --> 00:17:52,613
Imagine the sunset there.

144
00:17:54,823 --> 00:17:56,867
I mean, if it works out.

145
00:17:57,951 --> 00:17:59,745
We'll help the environment,

146
00:17:59,828 --> 00:18:01,789
and help their love life too.

147
00:18:01,872 --> 00:18:04,500
It's a win-win for us, right?

148
00:18:04,583 --> 00:18:07,086
Wingman! Nice!

149
00:18:07,169 --> 00:18:08,212
That could work.

150
00:18:12,633 --> 00:18:13,801
There.

151
00:18:13,884 --> 00:18:14,885
Look.

152
00:18:15,427 --> 00:18:17,012
Maybe this place could work too.

153
00:19:00,639 --> 00:19:04,226
Quiet, fresh air. Beautiful.

154
00:19:04,309 --> 00:19:09,064
And most importantly, hours away
from that crazy woman.

155
00:19:10,149 --> 00:19:12,151
Only Chiara's missing.

156
00:19:12,234 --> 00:19:13,902
I wish she were here.

157
00:19:19,116 --> 00:19:21,326
At least there won't be any more

158
00:19:21,410 --> 00:19:24,037
random midnight meetings.

159
00:19:24,121 --> 00:19:26,456
No more obsession with A5 steak.

160
00:19:26,540 --> 00:19:30,669
No more world domination plans
in the middle of the night.

161
00:19:30,752 --> 00:19:32,796
Listen. Let's just smile.

162
00:19:32,880 --> 00:19:34,423
Help out when needed.

163
00:19:34,506 --> 00:19:36,049
Sightseeing.

164
00:19:36,133 --> 00:19:39,094
Then after we're back on shore,

165
00:19:39,178 --> 00:19:40,888
- after we settled,
- Donabel…

166
00:19:40,971 --> 00:19:41,930
Donabel!

167
00:19:46,226 --> 00:19:48,020
Good, you're here.

168
00:19:51,106 --> 00:19:51,940
Follow me.

169
00:19:53,108 --> 00:19:54,109
Let's go.

170
00:20:22,971 --> 00:20:24,223
If we're wrong,

171
00:20:24,306 --> 00:20:25,849
we create chaos.

172
00:20:25,933 --> 00:20:27,601
If we're right,

173
00:20:27,684 --> 00:20:30,020
they create even bigger chaos.

174
00:21:01,802 --> 00:21:03,971
Huh? I have my own room?

175
00:21:40,424 --> 00:21:41,675
People will move them.

176
00:22:55,832 --> 00:22:57,125
Sir, we have a proposal.

177
00:22:58,668 --> 00:23:01,505
Chiara wants to reconnect
with Viktor Valtrovi.

178
00:23:01,588 --> 00:23:03,215
- To get the information …
- No!

179
00:23:08,845 --> 00:23:10,097
Sir, please hear us out first.

180
00:23:12,474 --> 00:23:15,685
It's possible Viktor knows the locations
of La Morte Bianca's operations.

181
00:23:16,186 --> 00:23:18,438
And if we need to obtain information,

182
00:23:18,522 --> 00:23:20,190
then we have to consider it.

183
00:23:21,858 --> 00:23:24,277
<i>What you're asking me is,</i>

184
00:23:24,361 --> 00:23:26,071
<i>to allow Chiara,</i>

185
00:23:26,154 --> 00:23:31,701
<i>to reconnect with the same</i>
<i>criminal organization that raised her,</i>

186
00:23:31,785 --> 00:23:34,079
trained her, protected her,

187
00:23:34,746 --> 00:23:36,289
manipulated her.

188
00:23:36,373 --> 00:23:41,795
The very people who spent her entire life
telling her what's right and wrong.

189
00:23:43,505 --> 00:23:46,716
<i>And you want me to believe</i>
<i>they can't do that to her again?</i>

190
00:23:50,512 --> 00:23:51,680
Just one conversation.

191
00:23:51,763 --> 00:23:54,224
Just a clarification, just a talk.

192
00:23:54,307 --> 00:23:55,350
No feelings involved.

193
00:23:56,184 --> 00:23:57,644
It's like a toxic ex.

194
00:23:58,895 --> 00:24:01,690
Just a clarification, no feelings at all.

195
00:24:01,773 --> 00:24:03,608
But next thing you know,
they're back together.

196
00:24:03,692 --> 00:24:05,360
<i>Not because they're bad,</i>

197
00:24:05,443 --> 00:24:08,405
<i>but because they think they're in control.</i>

198
00:24:52,032 --> 00:24:53,909
What if Chiara is right?

199
00:24:53,992 --> 00:24:56,203
And even Viktor still cares?

200
00:24:56,286 --> 00:24:59,247
I notice that there are
cars roaming around here.

201
00:24:59,331 --> 00:25:01,458
Even motorcycles riding in tandem.

202
00:25:01,541 --> 00:25:04,169
Actually even people are wandering here.

203
00:25:04,252 --> 00:25:05,879
<i>I don't feel good about it.</i>

204
00:25:12,135 --> 00:25:14,179
I want to talk to Papa.

205
00:25:24,689 --> 00:25:26,942
Of course I also want to give something.

206
00:25:31,988 --> 00:25:34,157
- What happened?
- <i>I slept so well.</i>

207
00:25:36,076 --> 00:25:38,245
Hold on, where are Mikoy and Chiara?
